[Git] Unstage all files (Undo 'git add .') :: git restore --staged .
[Git] Unstage a specific file :: git restore --staged <file>
[Git] Edit the most recent commit message :: git commit --amend
[Git] Edit an older or multiple commits (interactive) :: git rebase -i HEAD~3
[Git] START interactive rebase (edit/squash/reword) for last 3 commits :: git rebase -i HEAD~3
[Git-Rebase] (Editor) Use commit as-is (default) :: pick
[Git-Rebase] (Editor) Stop to edit commit message ONLY :: reword
[Git-Rebase] (Editor) Stop to edit files AND message (like --amend) :: edit
[Git-Rebase] (Editor) Combine/squash commit INTO previous commit (prompts for new message) :: squash
[Git-Rebase] (Editor) Combine/squash commit INTO previous commit (discards message) :: fixup
[Git-Rebase] (Editor) Delete the commit entirely :: drop
[Git-Rebase] (Terminal) AFTER making changes during an 'edit' stop :: git add . && git commit --amend
[Git-Rebase] (Terminal) Continue the rebase process :: git rebase --continue
[Git-Rebase] (Terminal) ABORT the rebase and return to original state :: git rebase --abort
[Git-Rebase] (Warning) This REWRITES history. Do NOT use on pushed/public branches.
